Subject: [PATCH] amdgpu/psp: flush HDP in the fence-wait loop + raise psp_timeout

AthenaOS runs amdgpu as a userspace daemon and CPU-maps the APU VRAM carveout
UNCACHED-direct (via SYS_LINUXKPI_MAP_PHYS), not through the GPU BAR + HDP the
way an in-kernel driver does. The PSP writes its completion fence to that
carveout DRAM; without draining the GPU HDP write path the fence becomes
CPU-visible only ~18 s later (LOAD_TOC completed using 18750 of the 20000
timeout iterations; SETUP_TMR then just exceeded it and psp_load_fw failed
-EINVAL, blocking all of PSP hw_init).

Add an explicit amdgpu_device_flush_hdp() alongside the existing invalidate in
psp_cmd_submit_buf's poll loop so the fence lands immediately, and raise
psp_timeout as a safety margin. On real hardware flush_hdp is a cheap register
write (hdp_v6_0 amdgpu_hdp_generic_flush) and a no-op on the coherent side, so
this is safe for the in-kernel path too.

--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_psp.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_psp.c
@@ -276,7 +276,7 @@ static int psp_early_init(struct amdgpu_ip_block *ip_block)

 	psp->adev = adev;

-	adev->psp_timeout = 20000;
+	adev->psp_timeout = 60000;

 	psp_check_pmfw_centralized_cstate_management(psp);

@@ -736,6 +736,10 @@ psp_cmd_submit_buf(struct psp_context *psp,
 		if (ras_intr)
 			break;
 		usleep_range(60, 100);
+		/* AthenaOS: drain the GPU HDP write path so the PSP's fence write
+		 * to (uncached-mapped) carveout DRAM is visible now, not ~18s
+		 * later. Cheap register write on hw; no-op on the coherent side. */
+		amdgpu_device_flush_hdp(psp->adev, NULL);
 		amdgpu_device_invalidate_hdp(psp->adev, NULL);
 	}

